/PERSON> said his paper was prompted by April sermons by general authorities which, in their warnings about `` alternate voices'' within the church, `` sought to inflict upon us a kind of spiritual lobotomy in order to keep us docile and submissive.'' Mormons are taught that their leaders from founder <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON> to the present are divinely inspired prophets whose pronouncements carry the weight of scripture. <PERSON> Edwin </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Firmage </PERSON>, a law professor at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Utah </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Mormon </ORGANIZATION> scholar, shocked many church members with his suggestion in June that women be ordained to the priesthood.
