 <ORGANIZATION> KLM </ORGANIZATION>'s agreements with <ORGANIZATION> Wings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> were drafted on a conservative basis so as to guarantee that <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> would remain an American carrier with American management and with American crews flying American aircraft on American routes,'' the statement said. A senior <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> has the option of either having <ORGANIZATION> KLM </ORGANIZATION> withdraw $ 224 million of its investment or increasing total equity in the airline so <ORGANIZATION> KLM </ORGANIZATION>'s share is cut to 25 percent. <PERSON> Checchi </PERSON> said he already has had several offers and saw no problem with finding new investors. The agreement with the <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> also requires regular reports on <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION>'s finances, a reflection of department concern for the $ 3.1 million debt the takeover imposed on the carrier.
