<TEXT>
 One death reported, and property damages estimated at $ 60 million. Nearly 45 percent of buildings were damaged, leaving 760 people homeless. Sugar crop seriously affected and some hotels forced to close temporarily. Full water and power to the islands' 46,000 residents should be restored next week.
